From: Jani Nikula <jani.nikula@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 8 Mar 2024 18:03:40 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] drm/panel: do not return negative error codes from
 drm_panel_get_modes()
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.8.3
Git-commit: fc4e97726530241d96dd7db72eb65979217422c9

[ Upstream commit fc4e97726530241d96dd7db72eb65979217422c9 ]

None of the callers of drm_panel_get_modes() expect it to return
negative error codes. Either they propagate the return value in their
struct drm_connector_helper_funcs .get_modes() hook (which is also not
supposed to return negative codes), or add it to other counts leading to
bogus values.

On the other hand, many of the struct drm_panel_funcs .get_modes() hooks
do return negative error codes, so handle them gracefully instead of
propagating further.

Return 0 for no modes, whatever the reason.

